<title>USA: InVision bomb scanners bought for Heathrow.</title>
<headline>InVision bomb scanners bought for Heathrow.</headline>
<dateline>FOSTER CITY, Calif. 1996-09-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>InVision Technologies Inc, a maker of airport bomb detection systems, said Monday the British Airport Authority had purchased three InVision CTX 5000 units for Heathrow International Airport.</p>
<p>The devices will scan checked luggage for explosives. The purchase contract provides for a multi-year service agreement.</p>
<p>Financial details were not disclosed.</p>
<p>Two units are set for delivery in the 1996 fourth quarter and one unit will be delivered in 1997, InVision said.</p>
<p>One CTX 5000 unit is already in operation at Heathrow.</p>
<p>Invision's stock was up 1-5/8 at 25 in early afternoon.</p>
